member.name: T:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.GeneralPurposeBitFlag
member.summary: Represents general purpose bit flag in the ZIP File Format Specification v6.3.3, #4.4.4.

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.GeneralPurposeBitFlag.FileIsEncrypted
member.summary: Bit 0: If set, indicates that the file is encrypted.

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.GeneralPurposeBitFlag.ZeroLocalHeader
member.summary: Bit 3: If this bit is set, the fields crc-32, compressed size and uncompressed size are set to zero in the local header. The correct values are put in the data descriptor immediately following the compressed data.
member.remarks: Note: PKZIP version 2.04g for DOS only recognizes this bit for method 8 compression, newer versions of PKZIP recognize this bit for any compression method.

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.GeneralPurposeBitFlag.ReservedForEnhancedDeflating
member.summary: Bit 4: Reserved for use with method 8, for enhanced deflating.

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.GeneralPurposeBitFlag.CompressedPatchedData
member.summary: Bit 5: If this bit is set, this indicates that the file is compressed patched data.
member.remarks: Note: Requires PKZIP version 2.70 or greater.

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.GeneralPurposeBitFlag.StrongEncryption
member.summary: Bit 6: Strong encryption. If this bit is set, you MUST set the version needed to extract value to at least 50 and you MUST also set bit 0. If AES encryption is used, the version needed to extract value MUST be at least 51. See the section describing the Strong Encryption Specification for details. Refer to the section in this document entitled "Incorporating PKWARE Proprietary Technology into Your Product" for more information.

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.GeneralPurposeBitFlag.EncodingUtf8
member.summary: Bit 11: Language encoding flag (EFS). If this bit is set, the filename and comment fields for this file MUST be encoded using UTF-8 (see APPENDIX D).

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.GeneralPurposeBitFlag.HideLocalHeader
member.summary: Bit 13: Set when encrypting the Central Directory to indicate selected data values in the Local Header are masked to hide their actual values. See the section describing the Strong Encryption Specification for details. Refer to the section in this document entitled "Incorporating PKWARE Proprietary Technology into Your Product" for more information.

member.name: T:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.ImplodingFlags
member.summary: Represents general purpose bit flag for the Method 6 - Imploding ZIP File Format Specification v6.3.3, #4.4.4.

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.ImplodingFlags.SlidingDictionary8K
member.summary: For Method 6 - Imploding. Bit 1: If the compression method used was type 6, Imploding, then this bit, if set, indicates an 8K sliding dictionary was used. If clear, then a 4K sliding dictionary was used.

member.name: F:Telerik.WinForms.Spreadsheet.Zip.ImplodingFlags.ShannonFano3
member.summary: For Method 6 - Imploding. Bit 2: If the compression method used was type 6, Imploding, then this bit, if set, indicates 3 Shannon-Fano trees were used to encode the sliding dictionary output. If clear, then 2 Shannon-Fano trees were used.
